{
  "stem": "1292.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What about in the schools?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did-- when I was a little girl, I remember one teacher in particular.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was in infant school, and her son was a priest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she loved me very much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was her favorite.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So those are glimpses which I remember.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If anything, it did make me more united with the people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it did make me realize that it's something-- I always did feel very deeply that something should be done, that we have a homeland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that we are not just guests to be insulted whenever they wish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And therefore, I did join a Zionist movement as a young girl called [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Akiva. ?] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was a great atmosphere and wonderful feeling for looking into the future.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I did love all the songs which they did sing, because they was full of hope, where the Yiddish songs were terribly sentimental and beautiful, but very sad.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that did make me very happy to join this movement.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember on many occasions-- [SOBBING] [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Terrible. ?] Crying with help that there is hope for Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we did have those beautiful songs, which I still remember, which were full of hope that people would go to Israel and-- [SOBBING] Stupid.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that Israel would eventuate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were terribly dedicated people which did-- it was some boys which were from very well-to-do homes and girls.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they were so dedicated to this purpose.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They did strip themselves of all the comfort.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And [SIGHS] they were the 'haluzim,' which only did sing of one thing, to go to Israel and do hard work.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
